{"abstract": "The plunge in oil prices provides a fresh rationale for a combination of Halliburton and its rival Baker Hughes, if Halliburton can find cost cuts, Kevin Allison of Reuters Breakingviews writes.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/11/14/some-back-of-the-envelope-calculations-in-deal-for-baker-hughes/", "snippet": "The plunge in oil prices provides a fresh rationale for a combination of Halliburton and its rival Baker Hughes, if Halliburton can find cost cuts, Kevin Allison of Reuters Breakingviews writes.", "lead_paragraph": "Baker Hughes may be worth more than investors think. Shares of the No. 3 American oilfield services firm rose 15 percent on Thursday after news broke of deal talks with the No. 2 company, Halliburton. A back-of-the-envelope calculation suggests that Halliburton, worth $46 billion, should be willing to pay nearly 40 percent more than Baker Hughes\u2019 $22 billion undisturbed market valuation to seal a deal.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/15/business/dbpix-halliburton/dbpix-halliburton-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 383, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/11/15/business/dbpix-halliburton/dbpix-halliburton-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 383}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/15/business/dbpix-halliburton/dbpix-halliburton-jumbo.jpg", "height": 654, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/11/15/business/dbpix-halliburton/dbpix-halliburton-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1308, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "cred